@@$TJvSpecialImage
<TITLE TJvSpecialImage overview>
<GROUP JVCL.Graphics>
  TJvSpecialImage is an image that can be used to create special effects. 
  
  For example, you can use the methods FadeIn, and FadeOut to let an image slowly appear and disappear 
  on the form. The same effect can be accomplished by using the property Brightness, which sets the 
  brightness of the image. Set Stretch to True to reduce flickering.
  
  Use the Flipped and Mirrored to flip the image vertically or horizontally. Use Inverted to invert
  the image.
  
  Call Reset to restore the image to it's original state. 
