@@TJvSpecialImage
<GROUP TJvSpecialImage>
Summary
  Supports extended features such as fade in, fade out and image flipping.
Description
  Use TJvSpecialImage to create image special effects. For example, you can use the methods FadeIn, 
  and FadeOut to let an image slowly appear and disappear on the form. The same effect can be 
  accomplished by using the property Brightness, which sets the brightness of the image.
  
  Use the Flipped and Mirrored to flip the image vertically or horizontally. Use Inverted to invert
  the image.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpecialImage.Create
Summary
  Creates and initializes an instance of TJvSpecialImage.
Description
  Call Create to create an instance of TJvSpecialImage at runtime. A TJvSpecialImage component placed on a 
  form at design time is created automatically.

  Pass a single Component as a parameter to provide the image with an Owner that is responsible
  for freeing it.

  Create calls the inherited Create method, then sets the initial values for the image as follows: 

  * Brightness is set to 100.
  * Inverted is set to False.
  * Flipped is set to False.
  * Mirrored is set to False.
Parameters
  AOwner - The owner for the instance of TJvScrollbar.
See Also
  Brightness, Destroy, Flipped, Inverted, Mirrored
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpecialImage.Destroy
Summary
  Destroys an instance of TJvSpecialImage.
Description
  Do not call Destroy directly in an application. Instead, call Free. Free verifies that the 
  TJvSpecialImage object is not nil and only then calls Destroy.
Parameters
  None.
See Also
  Create
